  "date_encoding": "days_since_epoch_1970",
  "summary": "Storage design optimized for TPC-H Q1, Q3, Q6 workload. Focus on three active tables: lineitem (fact, 6M rows), orders (dimension, 1.5M rows), customer (dimension, 150K rows). Key design decisions: (1) Sorted indexes on date columns (lineitem.l_shipdate, orders.o_orderdate) to accelerate range-based temporal filters present in all queries. (2) Hash indexes on all join keys (l_orderkey, o_orderkey, o_custkey, c_custkey) to enable efficient hash joins in Q3's star schema. (3) Hash index on customer.c_mktsegment for selective equality filtering. (4) Columnar storage groups hot columns (date filters, revenue calculation columns: l_extendedprice, l_discount) together for cache efficiency. (5) All dates stored as int32_t (days since epoch) for fast integer comparison. (6) Inactive tables (nation, region, supplier, part, partsupp) excluded from design as they have zero access frequency. This design prioritizes analytical scan performance on lineitem while supporting efficient joins through hash indexes."
